    {
      "id": "7ac51681807bf7b6993ba83c66a7aa75536e31f8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-07 20:54:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Oleg, can you please also fix \"lfs-heat_set.1\" to reference \"lfs-heat_get.1\" instead of \"lfs-heat.1\".  I noticed this while running \"mandb\" to rebuild the \"whatis\" database.\n\nbtw a vaguely related question.\n\nWe have some inconsistency with lctl snapshot commands.\nthey commands are lctl snapshot_xxx but the man pages are lctl-snapshot-xxx and inside they are referenced as such too, e.g.:\n\n.TH LCTL-SNAPSHOT_UMOUNT 8 \"2017-05-13\" Lustre \"configuration utilities\"\n.SH NAME\nlctl-snapshot_umount \\- unmount Lustre snapshot\n.SH SYNOPSIS\n.TP\n.B lctl snapshot_umount \\fR{-F | --fsname fsname} [-h | --help]\n              {-n | --name ssname} [-r | --rsh remote_shell]\n\n...\n\n.SH AVAILABILITY\n.B lctl-snapshot-umount\nis part of the\n.BR lustre (7)\nfilesystem package.\n.SH SEE ALSO\n.BR lctl (8),\n.BR lctl-lcfg (8),\n.BR lctl-barrier (8),\n.BR lctl-snapshot-create (8),\n.BR lctl-snapshot-destroy (8),\n.BR lctl-snapshot-modify (8),\n.BR lctl-snapshot-list (8),\n.BR lctl-snapshot-mount (8)\n\nso shouls all those snapshot- references be changed to snapshot_ and the files themselves renamed?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "9c2565b688626e4e35b83257f40f43ca490b4217",
      "tag": "autogenerated:gerrit:newPatchSet",
      "author": {
