    {
      "id": "bb3fb4795628da62af4c5cefa36de97390f3db16",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2024-08-07 21:36:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> so should all those snapshot- references be changed to snapshot_\n > and the files themselves renamed?\n\nHonestly, my preference for \"lctl snapshot_FOO\" would be to create a new \"lctl snapshot\" command and have \"FOO\" be a sub-command of that, and the same for \"lctl lfsck_FOO\" and similar (of course keeping the old commands for compatibility).\n\nFor these ones, having a .so reference with the snapshot_FOO names would probably be best for consistency:\n\n lctl-snapshot_FOO.8:\n .so man1/lctl-snapshot-FOO.8\n\nWe've done that with newer commands like \"lfs mirror FOO\", but I don't think we knew that was possible for older commands.  That avoids breaking the git history of the existing files, but makes them accessible by either name and will work if a subcommand is added.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
